notes: This was my one allowed "Redo" After we blew past the midpoint i looked for another key level, I found a low yesterday that we wicked out and retested again. I went ahead and jumped in for 3 shorts. This was very dangerous it seems due to volatility i had my stop loss way up in the orb incase we had to test it again to drop lower, Which we did. I went HEAVY into Drawdown but stayed disciplined and the trade reversed back down and worked out in my favor. I found another low we started to stall out aroun dso i clipped on contract off and waited to see but we kept retesting so i set my Stop loss to that point and it got tested again and price went back up to the upside.

checklistSnapshot.text: Is price action aligned with the higher timeframe bias and are you trading in that direction (not counter-trend revenge)?
Are you entering at a meaningful level (HTF level, clear liquidity area, FVG, etc.) with a clean trigger candle or pattern?
Is your stop in a logical place (not arbitrary) and is the reward-to-risk at least 2R with room for price to move cleanly?
Are you inside your allowed trading window and free of major news or random chop times for this instrument?
Are you calm, not tilted, and still inside your daily loss / max trades limits (no chasing, no FOMO, no 'one more')?

notes: Day number 8!!! Today i feel like this was my best trade yet, I stuck to my rules all the way through entry and a little draw down. Dont be scared of news, You are a Scalper, Trade the news dont predict it! I need to remember to only use 1 minute charts for entries and not for exits, That almost got me. I did clip one contract off after 1RR i held on to the other 2 contracts down to a key level and sold both off. I had two key levels marked out to the downside to take profit at and i am now seeing both levels are getting hit. I need to learn how to determine if a reversal is happening at level A or Level B. I still feel like this was my best trade ever, Good job bro.

notes: Day number 7!!!! So, Today we had news at 6:30 that shot price up pretty high, Waited for a Retrace back down to the ORB midpoint, We tapped it a few times i wanted one more confirmation and ended up disrespecting it. Once the price was disrespected i looked to Short to the bottom of the News candle at 6:30, That worked out perfectly. We actually kept going down, i could have held the short longer.

Day number 6!!! Tried to take a risk today, NY open shot up with no retest at all of the ORB. We got up to a point of consolidation i had conviction it was going to retrace back down to the mid point, It did not. I ended up taking a loss on a short, I panicked and flipped my position at 7002 and went long until 10:16am Where my trailed Stop ended up getting hit. I think there is opportunity for these additional entries after the ORB but we need a lot of practice.

Day number 5!!!! Cant believe we have another win! Today we had a decent amount of news, We blew up past the ORB before NY open, We eventually retraced back down and respected the orb multiple times so i went ahead and put a small risk 3 contract in, risked 20 dollars per contract. We went back up close to session highs and i actually meant to clip off one contract but i sold all 3 for a decent profit, Happy accident i wanted to be out of this all together by 8am for the News anyways! Look for smaller opportunities dude, We don't have to go for hundreds of dollars per contract. Arguably we could have left the small 60 dollar stop loss and let it ride a little higher but for a news day i am happy.

notes: Day number 4!!! This one was wild, I had a perfect Retest at the midpoint and a really good entry. Right after entering i hopped in a Stream and heard NQ was completely dumping when i just longed ES... Es did some very bad and choppy price action dropping all the way past the orb close to my 12 point stop and would retrace back up to around 15 points above. I tried to be paitent and see if we could do a little better but after we retraced to my mid point again and stalled out again 15 points up i clipped on contract off while in a meeting at work waited a little longer and basically the same thing happened again so i clipped the last two contracts off securing a win. EOD UPDATE: Price did not do really any better later in the day, I am very happy with my exit.
